                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">mediocre, irregular</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        Scribe: ʾAstǝʿa Dǝngǝl. ʾabuna
                        ʾAstǝʿa Dǝngǝl is mentioned as the scribe in the supplication formulas
                        throughout the Ms. (e.g., <locus target="#44vb">44vb</locus>, 57rb, 68va,
                           78ra).<date>Late 19th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; name of the
                           scribe; groups of lines on the incipit page of Texts I-1 and I-2; incipit
                           of (sub)sections; sometimes the first word of Text I-5; elements of the
                           punctuation signs and of the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
